/* Loy Krathong's Etymology & History sections disputes */ new section

Reverted the article! The editor Anuwater himself seems to be very nationalist and will not allow the fact written on this article. By the way, ALL the sources cited in the History>Origin section are all from Thai sources, none of them is Khmer source!!! (Check again) On the other hand, the etymology of word /krathong is obviously originated from Khmer word /kantong. Again kantong/krathong refers to "container made from (banana) leaves", NOT refers to "lamp" or "water lantern".
/* Question of the Accuracy of "Etymology" and "History" section */ new section

/* Origin */ Reaffirm the accuracy of the sources. The sources cited in this section are from Thai sources based on the recent studies of independent Thai historian and researchers, not from Khmer nationalist sources!!!

The previous editions are acts of vandalism!!! Those editions made earlier by previous editor didn't provide the accuracy of the text in reference to the sections edited. 1. In "Etymology" section, the source "Baxter-Sagart Old Chinese reconstruction" didn't mention the word "krathong" used in Thai is originated from Old Chinese. Whereas, the source "The /ka-/ and /kra-/ prefixes in Thai." confirmed the word "krathong" of being originated from Khmer.
